  "title": "Simple harmonic motion - compare forces",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block attached to a horizontal spring undergoes simple harmonic motion along a horizontal surface. When the block is at its maximum displacement, the force exerted on the block by the spring has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A\"><math alttext=\"F sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></math></span></span>, and when the block is at its equilibrium position, the force exerted on the block by the spring has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub equilibrium\"><math alttext=\"F sub equilibrium\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A\"><math alttext=\"F sub A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub equilibrium\"><math alttext=\"F sub equilibrium\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>eq</mi></msub></math></span></span>, and provides a valid justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A equals F sub equilibrium\"><math alttext=\"F sub A equals F sub equilibrium\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>eq</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the force is zero when the block is at its equilibrium position and when it is at its maximum displacement.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A equals F sub equilibrium\"><math alttext=\"F sub A equals F sub equilibrium\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>eq</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the force on the block is constant throughout the blockâ€™s motion.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A is greater than F sub equilibrium\"><math alttext=\"F sub A is greater than F sub equilibrium\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>eq</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the speed of the block is a maximum when the displacement is a maximum and zero when the displacement is zero.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A is greater than F sub equilibrium\"><math alttext=\"F sub A is greater than F sub equilibrium\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>eq</mtext></msub></math></span></span> because the force is zero at the equilibrium position and a maximum at maximum displacement.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
